<speech id="uk.org.publicwhip/wms/2008-06-18b.54WS.3" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/member/1423" speakername="Jack Straw" speakeroffice="The Secretary of State for Justice and Lord Chancellor" colnum="54WS"  url="http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm200708/cmhansrd/cm080618/wmstext/80618m0002.htm#08061893000095">
	<p pid="b.54WS.3/1">Today I have deposited copies of &quot;The Freedom of Information Act 2000&mdash;Third Annual Report on the operation of the Freedom of Information Act in Central Government&mdash;2007&quot; in the Libraries of both Houses. Copies are also available in the Vote Office and the Printed Paper Office and are available on the internet at:</p>
	<p pid="b.54WS.3/2" class="indent"><a href="http://www.justice.gov.uk/publications/freedomofinformationquarterly.htm">www.justice.gov.uk/publications/freedomofinformationquarterly.htm</a></p>
	<p pid="b.54WS.3/3">This is the third annual report analysing the performance of central Government in the third full year of freedom of information.</p>
</speech>
